# Model Conventions

## Field naming
- Use snake_case for all model fields
- ForeignKey fields: name by the related model (e.g., `subject`, `chapter`, `user`)
- JSON fields: use `JSONField` with `default=list` or `default=dict`, never `null=True`
- Timestamps: `auto_now_add=True` for creation, `auto_now=True` for updates

## Model inventory

| Model          | Parent     | Purpose                          | Key relationships                  |
|----------------|-----------|----------------------------------|------------------------------------|
| Subject        | —         | Top-level content category       | Has many chapters                  |
| Chapter        | Subject   | One chapter within a subject     | Has many questions + takeaways     |
| Question       | Chapter   | Interview question with answer   | Belongs to chapter                 |
| Takeaway       | Chapter   | Quick-recall summary item        | Belongs to chapter                 |
| Highlight      | User      | Text highlight in a chapter      | Belongs to user + chapter          |
| Note           | User      | User note (subject/chapter)      | Belongs to user, optional subject/chapter |
| StagedRequest  | User      | Proposed content change          | requested_by + reviewed_by users   |
| Subscription   | Subject   | DeltaMails email subscription    | Belongs to subject, optional user  |

## Ordering
- Always define `Meta.ordering`
- Subjects/Chapters/Questions/Takeaways: `order` field (PositiveIntegerField)
- User data (highlights, notes, staged requests): `-created_at` (newest first)

## String representation
- `__str__` must return something human-readable for Django Admin
- Chapters: `f"{self.subject.slug} Ch.{self.chapter_number}: {self.title}"`
- Questions: `f"Q{self.order}: {self.question[:80]}"`
- StagedRequests: `f"[{self.status}] {self.operation} {self.target_model} by {self.requested_by}"`

## StagedRequest model
- `operation`: create / update / delete
- `target_model`: subject / chapter / question / takeaway
- `target_id`: null for create (set after apply), required for update/delete
- `payload`: JSONField storing the model fields to create/update
- `status`: pending → approved (via `apply()`) or rejected (via `reject()`)
- `apply(reviewer)`: executes the operation, sets status to approved
- `reject(reviewer, note)`: sets status to rejected with optional note

## User-scoped models
- Always include `user = models.ForeignKey(settings.AUTH_USER_MODEL, on_delete=models.CASCADE)`
- Highlights and Notes are user-scoped — never expose across users
- StagedRequest: users see own requests, admins see all

## Migrations
- Run `makemigrations` after every model change
- Review migration files before committing
- Never manually edit migration files unless fixing a conflict

## Admin registration
- Every model gets registered in `admin.py`
- Use `list_display` with 3-5 useful columns
- Use `list_filter` for ForeignKey fields and choice fields
- Use inline admin classes for parent-child relationships (Chapter → Questions)
- StagedRequest admin: color-coded status badges, JSON payload preview, bulk approve/reject actions
- Subscription admin: list with email, subject, difficulty, is_active; "Send test DeltaMail" action
